The only prerequisite other than nodejs in order to run this NPM package is MongoDB.
Please be sure to install MongoDB with a new user and an empty database!


1. Update mongodb variables in env.txt
2. run the command `npm install`
3. Use autostart method of your choice to autostart the server with `npm start`

You can run npm start manually and visit https://localhost:3000 to visit 








Below are some helpful console commands useful for the lazy coder

execute `mongo` in terminal
after successful connection execute:
	use admin
	db.createUser(
	  {
		user: "admin",
		pwd: "ENTERPASSWORDHERE",
		roles: [ { role: "userAdminAnyDatabase", db: "admin" } ]
	  }
	)



#!/bin/sh
# This script uses (not included) Let's Encrypt certificates with a validity < 30 days

if ! letsencrypt renew > /var/log/letsencrypt/renew.log 2>&1 ; then
    echo Automated renewal failed:
    cat /var/log/letsencrypt/renew.log
    exit 1
fi
/usr/sbin/nginx -t && /usr/sbin/nginx -s reload && pm2 restart all



